What this file is used for
reads a stored summary from minio
takes a CID
builds the object key
fetches the .md file
returns the markdown text
What it does
connects to minio using config
uses the bucket from config
looks for:summary/cids/{cid}.md

checks whether the object exists
reads the content
returns:summary text
or error

Why this file exists
because analyticsapi needs real storage-reading code
domain/narrative.go only defined the contract
this file is the actual implementation of that contract
Why placed under internal/analyticsapi/
because this logic belongs to the analyticsapi service
it is not shared project-wide logic
it is API-side summary retrieval logic
Why under gateways/
because it talks to an external system
external system here = minio / object store
gateways/ is for I/O / outside-world interaction
Why under gateways/repos/ and not just gateways/
gateways/ would also work
repos/ is more specific
it signals:this file is about stored data access
this acts like repository-style retrieval

so:gateways/ = broad external interaction bucket
gateways/repos/ = external data-storage access specifically
